subject: Updated keyboard mappings, and examples for Out and Ooze
msgSnippet: I ve updated the spreadsheet with the keyboard mapping proposals, this time calling it qs_keybd_proposals2.csv . From now on, I ll indicate a version number
messageBody:
I've updated the spreadsheet with the keyboard mapping proposals, this
time calling it 'qs_keybd_proposals2.csv'. From now on, I'll indicate
a version number both in the file name and in the first line of the
file. I hope that will make it easier to track changes. It's nice to
retain some history, but I won't leave more than two old versions of
the file on the site. This version includes the swap of #37 and #40 in
BPJ2, and the swap of #10 and #39 in QS-Nu. Benct explained his change
earlier. The change to QS-Nu brings it in line with the other
proposals for those letters.

For comparison of the assignments of #37 and #40, here are the
examples Benct came up with earlier (if I remember correctly):

How is your house in town?
Few humane beauties are fooled by cute dudes in suits.

Using each proposal:

Jerome kbd:
{hQ z jr hQs iG tQn?
fjM hjMmEG bjMtIz r fMld bF kjMt dMdz iG sMts.}

QS-SAMPA:
{hH z jr hHs Iq tHn?
fju hjumeq bjutiz r fuld bY kjut dudz Iq suts.}

Peter Guinness:
{hW z yr hWs iM tWn?
fyU hyUmAM byUtEz r fUld bI kyUt dUdz iM sUts.}

BPJ2:
{hU z yr hUs iN tUn?
fyB hyBmEN byBtIz r fBld bY kyBt dBdz iN sBts.}

QS-Nu:
{hP z yr hPs iN tPn?
fyU hyUmEN byUtIz r fUld bY kyUt dUdz iN sUts.}

Moira:
{hQ z Yr hQs iM tQn?
fYU hYUmAM bYUtEz r fUld bI kYUt dUdz iM sUts.}

Comments:
1) I think I like Q for #37 after looking at the mappings of the first
sentence...
2) I don't like B for #40 at all. Please, Benct, let's revert that one.

Ted
